14 SECTION 2. EXEMPTION - TRANSFERS. Notwithstanding section 54-16-04, the director
15 of the office of management and budget shall transfer appropriation authority between line items
16 of the legislative management and legislative council as may be requested by the chairman of
17 the legislative management or the director of the legislative council upon the finding by the
18 chairman or the director that the nature of studies and duties assigned to the legislative
19 management or legislative council requires the transfers in properly carrying on the legislative
20 management's and legislative council's functions and duties. The director of the office of
21 management and budget shall similarly make transfers of appropriation authority between the
22 line items for the sixty-ninth and seventieth legislative assemblies, upon request by the
23 chairman of the legislative management or the director of the legislative council upon the finding
24 by the chairman or director that the transfers are required for the legislative assembly to carry
25 on its functions and duties.
